Performance Considerations

1. Cold Start vs Warm Start:
   · Cold start: Download + decompression (few seconds)
   · Warm start: Cache hit (milliseconds)
2. Cache Strategy:
   · Use local disk cache (/tmp in Lambda or SageMaker)
   · Implement TTL or size-based eviction if needed
   · Consider using ElastiCache for multi-instance environments
3. Compression Choice:
   · Use zstandard for best balance of compression and speed
   · Use lz4 if decompression speed is critical
   · Test both with your specific data to make the final decision

Deployment Recommendations

1. Memory Allocation:
   · Ensure your SageMaker instances have enough memory for cached embeddings
   · Monitor memory usage in CloudWatch
2. Monitoring:
   · Log download and decompression times
   · Set up CloudWatch alarms for slow operations
   · Monitor cache hit rates
3. Cost Optimization:
   · Use S3 Intelligent-Tiering for embeddings
   · Consider S3 One Zone-IA for non-critical embeddings
   · Implement lifecycle policies to archive old versions

This approach gives you the best of both worlds: efficient storage with fast access times. The local caching ensures that after the first load, subsequent requests are extremely fast, making it suitable for production workloads.
